<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Adjunct1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Adjunct,</orth> adj. attending, consequent: <cit><quote>though death be a.</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 133</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>every humour hath his a. pleasure,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son xci.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 91, 5</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>though that my death were a. to my act,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 3.3" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 3, 57</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>